    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classostk_1_1mathematics_1_1curvefitting_1_1_interpolator" kindref="compound">Interpolator</ref> (abstract class) </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>In mathematics, an interpolator is a type of estimator allowing to construct new data points based on a range of a discrete set of known data points.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".cpp"><codeline><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>interpolator<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classostk_1_1mathematics_1_1curvefitting_1_1_interpolator_1a41019cdd1cad7b5c5c818ff25a122536" kindref="member">Interpolator::GenerateInterpolator</ref>(<ref refid="classostk_1_1mathematics_1_1curvefitting_1_1_interpolator_1a6318ad43cbddfa9b220213af2ac33557a32a843da6ea40ab3b17a3421ccdf671b" kindref="member">Interpolator::Type::Linear</ref>,<sp/>x,<sp/>y);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">double</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>value<sp/>=<sp/>interpolator-&gt;evaluate(1.5);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><ulink url="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpolator">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpolator</ulink>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
